related_items.title: Aerial photographs of the Middle East
description: 24 photographic prints : gelatin silver ; 17 x 23 cm. | Predominately aerial photographs showing villages, cities, coastlines, rivers, harbors, deserts and other geographic features primarily in Jordan, Iraq, and Egypt.  Also shown are bridges, airports, biplanes, and flying boats (seaplanes).  Locations include the Pyramids at Jīzah (Gizeh), the Suez Canal, Alexandria, the Nile Valley, and Cairo in Egypt; the Gaza Aerodome, the Gulf of Akaba (Aqaba), Baghdad, Iraq, and the ancient of city of Petra in Jordan, and Buṣrá al-Shām in Syria. Albert I, King of Belgium in an airplane is also shown.

related_items.title: Photographs of architectural monuments in Jerusalem, Syria, and Egypt
description: 1 album (42 gelatin silver prints) ; 31 x 22 cm. (album) | Photographs show architectural monuments in Jerusalem, Syria, and Egypt. Album page image number: 1-19: (p. 1-21) Photographs in Jerusalem include: the Damascus Gate, St. Stephen's Gate, Saracenic arch at Bab Es-Silseleh, Dome of the Rock (western porch, tiles, mosque interior, rotunda, stained glass window, mosaics, and dome interior), Mosque el-Aksa (al-Aqsa), and cedar pulpit. Also includes image of the mosque over the Cave of Machpelah (Cave of the Patriarchs), Hebron. Album page image number 20-42: (p. 22-44) Photographs in Syria include: waterwheel at Hama, mosque at Ḥimṣ, the Great Mosque in Damascus, and mosques and castle, Mameluke tomb, minaret in market quarter, finely carved  window, Arabic capitals (Jami el-Adliyeh), and Khan el-Vezir in Aleppo. In Egypt: mosques of Mohammed Ali, Kait Bey, and Emir Akhor, and tombs of Mameluks in Cairo.
